    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... it doesn't feel like a spirit screaming for change. it feels more like just... entropy. like everything that made me \"me\" has just withered away and there's nothing left to rebuild. it's just a hollow, heavy weight. sometimes i look at the clock and think, i've already lived my life, the rest is just... waiting for the lights to go out. is there really any point in trying to \"build\" something on top of nothingness?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
